chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Lymphoma and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
You must tell DVLA about your lymphoma if:

  • you develop problems with your brain or nervous system
  • your doctor has expressed concerns about your fitness to drive
  • you can only drive a specially adapted vehicle or a certain type of vehicle
  • your medication causes side effects that might make it unsafe for you to drive

Fill in form C1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
